{"word":"H235 - אָזַל - ʼâzal - aw-zal' - Fail","slug":"H235","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אָזַל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼâzal"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>aw-zal'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Fail"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05D6;&#x05DC; - 'a&#x0302;zal</b> - <i>aw-zal'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>go away</i>, hence to <i>disappear: - </i>fail, gad about, go to and fro [but in <a href='B:330 27:19'>Eze 27:19</a> the word is rendered by many &ldquo;from Uzal,&rdquo; by others &ldquo;yarn&rdquo;], be gone (spent)."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H187\">H187</a>, <a href=\"#/H237\">H237</a>"}]}